A group led by Halcyon Investments,a New York securities and risk arbitrage partnership, said ithas acquired 486,400 shares of Atlantic Research Corp, or 6.4pct of the total outstanding common stock.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,the Halcyon group said it bought the stake for 15.6 mln dlrsfor no specific purpose.    The group said it has no plans to seek control of AtlanticResearch, which has been sought by Clabir Corp &lt;CLG>, but saidit may buy more stock or sell some or all of what it has. Reuter&#3;